1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What's up?

2
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What?

3
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Suraiyya came here,

4
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Met neither of us,

5
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And took Ammi Begum into the room.

6
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who am I?

7
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Come.

8
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Where?

9
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Out in the sun.

10
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Sit for a while.

11
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mehru...

12
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
When did you start talking like Ammi Begum?

13
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ever since I realised

14
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That she says only what's best.

15
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Merci beaucoup.

16
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I talked to her as a mother last night.

17
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I said,

18
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'You asked for time'.

19
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'It was our fault'

20
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'That we didn't ask you how long you wanted'.

21
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She looked back, surprised.

22
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She couldn't believe I was saying that!

23
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Then, she said,

24
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'About'...

25
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'2 or 4 days'?

26
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I didn't stop there.

27
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I said, 'Even if you don't accept',

28
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Don't refuse'.

29
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't keep someone waiting so many years just to refuse...

30
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't you think it's a job well done?

31
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What about him?

32
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who?

33
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The one who'll leave me tongue-tied in the doghouse.

34
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You take care of him.

35
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
A lad spoilt in the West can't be corrected in the East.

36
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
As if he were ever...

37
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't you say it?

38
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Loafer, wastrel, Londoner tramp'!

39
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I lie about it.

40
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So that no one except Jiya likes him.

41
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Now, I've even started believing it.

42
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He's a loafer... A wastrel...

43
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The Londoner tramp!

44
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why, Ammi Begum?

45
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why do you lie?

46
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I hope to keep

47
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
One promise, at the very least...

48
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That I'm saved from being tongue-tied in the doghouse or from the doghouse if not.

49
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What's going on, Maheen?

50
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It drives me crazy...

51
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've never seen it like this!

52
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The Granny doesn't like it when two cousins are making peace.

53
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The lad's Aunt didn't let him in when he brought flowers and perfume,

54
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
When everyone's thinking about him,

55
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That he better be married off to someone he doesn't even love!

56
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What the devil is going on?

57
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No idea.

58
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But I do know

59
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That it'll be fine if I agreed to marry Gulrez.

60
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why don't you?

61
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I have, Fajr.

62
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But my heart doesn't.

63
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Fantastic...

64
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Sometimes, I begin to curse my heart.

65
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I mean, whatever's wrong with Gulrez?

66
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He looks nice,

67
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Is of good character,

68
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Does his 9-to-5 job...

69
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Loves me, too...

70
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And...

71
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We've been engaged since we were kids...

72
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What's the big deal...

73
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What?

74
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No idea...

75
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Forgive me but I don't like it one bit, Ammi Begum...

76
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum and daughter talk about everything in classified meetings,

77
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And Dastoor's called upon only to hear the decision.

78
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Put a sock in it...

79
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've called you for your advice,

80
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Not to order you.

81
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Leave it be.

82
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I know it well enough.

83
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I was called for 'advice' the last time as well, but it ended with an order.

84
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Would you sit,

85
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Or would you rather that I send you out?

86
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why wouldn't I sit?

87
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm someone too, after all!

88
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Orders, ma'am?

89
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mehru...

90
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I hope you remember

91
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What Munshi Alam Deen had said.

92
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I do.

93
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He'd said,

94
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'If he doesn't want to marry Jiya',

95
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Just prod and ask him'

96
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Who he wants to marry'.

97
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Nah, I don't intend to prod...

98
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But go, Dastoor, and ask him today.

99
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm sure his answer will put you on the rack.

100
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're very angry with me, right?

101
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Because I didn't obey you?

102
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You think I've left you helpless?

103
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No, Dado...

104
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And as for my respect and regard for you, I can even sacrifice my life for you.
-Cut to the chase...

105
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What do I say?

106
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've been asking myself why I just couldn't obey you.

107
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why can't I just marry Jiya...

108
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But I've realised today

109
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That I will never marry Jiya.

110
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who, then?

111
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Tell me, who do you want to marry?

112
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Maheen.

113
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's been so long!

114
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why are you so late?

115
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Gulrez wasn't well.

116
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He took a pill and went to bed.

117
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I was worried about what I'd do alone if things got bad.

118
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No...

119
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But you always drink a glass of water...

120
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What are you looking at?

121
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What happened?

122
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Sit.

123
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Dad used to say...

124
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
A mother's heart can also be found in daughters and sisters.

125
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But I don't think any mother would be so motherly as you are.

126
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So?

127
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Which is why I'm sometimes afraid of you.

128
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Please, don't fear me...

129
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Or the mother in me.

130
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just speak your heart out.

131
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You wouldn't be able to hear it.

132
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm a mother, right?

133
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Let me tell you

134
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That the Lord gives mothers courage unlike any other.

135
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
C'mon!

136
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The worry kills me!

137
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Waqar Ahmed has made it clear that he'll marry Maheen.

138
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So? I mean --

139
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
As if Waqar Ahmed's words are a Royal edict

140
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That must be followed!

141
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yes.

142
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It is a Royal edict now.

143
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That's what we've been fearing.

144
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We?

145
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
All of us.

146
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Uncle Dastoor, Aunt Suraiyya, me...

147
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And, most of all, Ammi Begum...

148
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
How hard we've tried that it not come to this!

149
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But, in all honesty, no amount of wits and wisdom can change what's willed.

150
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But she said she loves no one else!

151
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She said everything in it.

152
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She doesn't love Gulrez.

153
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>In the tale of love where do these turns come from</i>

154
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>In the tale of love where do these turns come from</i>

