<i>That those we hold dear to us are the ones who break our heart</i>

160
00:14:29,450 --> 00:14:31,666
The world's ending, is it?

161
00:14:34,581 --> 00:14:36,683
Had a nightmare?

162
00:14:37,873 --> 00:14:39,062
What, then?

163
00:14:39,062 --> 00:14:42,315
The King's gambit, Maheen!

164
00:14:42,315 --> 00:14:44,426
What do you mean?

165
00:14:44,426 --> 00:14:45,615
Who did it?

166
00:14:45,615 --> 00:14:46,906
Waqar.

167
00:14:49,303 --> 00:14:49,994
That's what you woke me up for?

168
00:14:49,994 --> 00:14:51,944
C'mon, now, back to bed!

169
00:14:51,944 --> 00:14:53,773
Not another word about him!

170
00:14:53,773 --> 00:14:55,500
As if you can sleep now!

171
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:56,313
I can!

172
00:14:56,313 --> 00:14:58,634
No need to tell me anything about him.

173
00:14:58,634 --> 00:15:03,064
Who he meets, what he does, which gambit he plays -- I want none of it!

174
00:15:03,064 --> 00:15:04,731
Really?

175
00:15:05,526 --> 00:15:07,467
As if I'm lying!

176
00:15:07,467 --> 00:15:09,287
I'll take my leave, then!

177
00:15:09,287 --> 00:15:11,094
Please!

178
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He's told Nano who he wants to marry.

179
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hey!

180
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Jiya, right?

181
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
One of them French girls?

182
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who?

183
00:15:41,311 --> 00:15:43,465
You'd die where you stand --

184
00:15:43,465 --> 00:15:45,701
I mean -- where you sit -- if you heard it.

185
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
One of Nano's maids, is it?

186
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It doesn't matter to you, right, who he marries?

187
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why should it?

188
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Sweet dreams, then.

189
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've heard your reply.

190
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Reply?

191
00:16:03,509 --> 00:16:04,840
What do you mean, Fajr?

192
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:07,172
Mum's the word!

193
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It ain't gonna remain hidden for long!

194
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Khushi Mohammad will give you the good news in the morning.

195
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Oh yeah?

196
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll ask in the morning myself.

197
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He said

198
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That he'll only marry Maheen Aurangzeb!

199
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've decided...

200
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That the property will be divided tomorrow.

201
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And next week,

202
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We'll give him his share and send him to London forever.

203
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Forgive me, Ammi Begum,

204
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But this is no solution.

205
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Do you have a better solution?

206
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll talk to Maheen.

207
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No one will talk to Maheen.

208
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She'll never agree to marry Waqar.

209
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What if she did?

210
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm her mother, Ammi Begum.

211
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I should know, too,

212
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What else I don't know about my daughter!

213
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If there were any such thing, I would've gotten wind of it.

214
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I know very well

215
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That she'll create a ruckus over it.

216
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It just can't be!

217
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The girl's interested in someone, and the mother hasn't the foggiest!

218
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
How can that be?

219
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll ask Maheen.

220
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I tell you, she'll break his face for real.

221
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What are you looking at?

222
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't you believe me?

223
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Remember how they looked like mortal enemies?

224
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Now...

225
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Stay tuned for what they have in store...

226
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Are you worried?

227
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ashamed is more like it, Suraiyya...

228
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Strange

229
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That, after his parents died,

230
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He's asked his Dado for something for the first time,

231
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And Dado's so helpless

232
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That she can't give him anything except his piffling share.

233
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It'll be enough.

234
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Even if he's unhappy,

235
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm sure he'll settle for it if he saw his share.

236
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Forgive me, Mashood Ahmed...

237
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But you left Kaneez Begum to judge this perplexing matter,

238
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And to judge is to be so heartless

239
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
As to be blind to the grandson's wish...

240
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ever thought

241
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
How families come into being

242
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And stay together?

243
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What is it that makes us say firmly, 'These are our traditions',

244
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'And these are not'.

245
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Traditions are not built on casual exchanges of words,

246
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But by giving your word and honouring promises,

247
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Even if it means laying down your life,

248
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And, in the interest of fairness and justice,

249
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
By throttling your own wishes.

250
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I know what you're here to tell me.

251
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But you don't know that it's just a wish.

252
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I haven't insisted that it be fulfilled.

253
00:21:49,665 --> 00:21:51,230
Splendid!

254
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What a wish!

255
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
More like a bombshell you dropped on all of us!

256
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You've left many out of breath and many more gasping anxiously.

257
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And you're here acting like you're innocent!

258
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Got a signal from the other side?

259
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Signal?

260
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't tell me that 'signal' means just a signal in London.

261
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I mean...

262
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The green light, you know. Doesn't it mean something else?

263
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Of course. It's like, 'Go ahead'!

264
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So, ol' chap, did Maheen say, 'Go ahead'?

265
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Blimey, Uncle... Who knows what you're saying...

266
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Told her?

267
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who?

268
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Maheen, of course!

269
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She doesn't have the foggiest.

270
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
How do you know?

271
00:22:54,398 --> 00:22:58,929
Turn back before this very instant if you value your life!

272
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'd even say, go and tell Ammi Begum

273
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That you were kidding.

274
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I meant every bit of it.

275
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But if you want that Maheen marry Gulrez,

276
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I have no objections.

277
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I haven't challenged the family by telling you my wish,

278
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Nor insisted that you change your decisions.

279
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Do what you've promised.

280
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Congratulations.

281
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Another one's desires have been sacrificed on the altar of 'justice'.

282
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hearing you, I figure

283
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Maheen wants the same.

284
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She doesn't even want to see my face!

285
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She --

286
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I just felt if there's anyone I should marry, it's Maheen.

287
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Can you keep it locked in your heart forever?

288
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Of course.

289
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Where could it go if let out?

290
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I can't speak a word before her, let alone let my heart talk!

291
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just helpless feelings, Uncle...

292
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Can be chained now...

293
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Nobody hears a word if a kid's strangled the moment he's born.

294
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What do I tell Ammi Begum?

295
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Anything, really.

296
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But please, don't say that I was kidding.

297
00:24:48,152 --> 00:24:52,409
Feelings can be locked away...

298
00:24:52,409 --> 00:24:54,831
But not the truth, Uncle.

299
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Here's your tie.

300
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No need.

301
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why?

302
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You don't go to office without one.

303
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm not going to office.

304
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Then?

305
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm going to meet Nano.

306
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It --

307
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Would be better if you didn't... For a few days...

308
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why?

309
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just -- Don't...

310
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why are you stopping me?

311
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Wait for Maheen's reply.

312
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I don't know why, but I have this feeling that if you went to Nano's,

313
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She'd feel that you're there to beg...

314
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I never beg.

315
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You know that.
-They don't. Maheen doesn't.

316
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That's what she'll think.

317
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She won't.

318
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I won't let her.

319
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why must you be so adamant?

320
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I had a nightmare last night.

321
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Somewhere, in the eye of the storm...

322
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're shutting the doors and windows...

323
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're waiting

324
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
For Wali...

325
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Then, there's a knock on the door...

326
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You open the door.

327
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's Wali...

328
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You ask him to come in quickly,

329
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And shut the door.

330
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Wali's quiet...

331
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Almost unusually...

332
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Shocked...

333
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Distressed...

334
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You take out a bottle of cold water from the fridge.

335
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Give it to him...

336
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He gestures a no...

337
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Even though...

338
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He always has a glass when he gets back...

339
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So you heard everything?

340
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I thought you'd dozed off after taking the pill.

341
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'd actually dozed off.

342
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'd taken the pill.

343
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Enough of your theatrics.

344
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You heard everything.

345
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I don't listen in on you and Wali.

346
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Oh?

347
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So you really had this dream?

348
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Go on, then.

349
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll tell the rest to Nano.

350
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So that's why you're going...

351
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No.

352
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm going to tell her I won't marry Maheen.

353
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What rubbish!
-Not rubbish...

354
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I saw that you

355
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Were very worried.

356
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The sister's mask had fallen off your face...

357
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Revealing every bit of the mother.

358
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The mother worried by every cough of her child...

359
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What've you become?

360
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've decided...

361
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That I won't be the kid

362
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who'd ask his Mum for the moon to play with.

363
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I just want the moonlight.

364
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What'd he say?

365
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He said he wants to get even with you.

366
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He might've been joking.

367
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He'd joke about marrying me?

368
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just ask him.

369
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He may be serious.

370
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll feed him his teeth!

371
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That's what you ought to do.

372
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What?

373
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Feed him his teeth!

374
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I do what I say, Mum.

375
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ah,

376
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So you're waiting to finish breakfast, eh?

377
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Do you have any idea what she'd do?

378
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yes.

379
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just what she ought to.

380
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
C'mon, finish your breakfast.

381
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hello?

382
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hello, Uncle Munshi.

383
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hello there.

384
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Give the phone to Ali.

385
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He's gone to school, Fajr.

386
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who goes to school on Doomsday?

387
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Anyway...

388
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Got a helmet?

389
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Helmet?

390
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Find one, Uncle, pronto!

391
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What'd you do with one?

392
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Jeez...

393
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Find one and give it to Waqar. Quick!

394
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Has he...

395
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Asked for one?

396
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No!

397
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's a gift from me!

398
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Good morning, Uncle Munshi.

399
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Morning.

400
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Where's Nano?

401
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
In her room.

402
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She doesn't come out very much these days.

403
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Gulrez!

404
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Waqar!

405
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
How are you?

406
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Fine.

407
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But, blimey, mate, it's been two months since I'm here, and we're meeting for the second time today!

408
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The third. Not the second.

409
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No way.

410
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We did.

411
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Last night, I met you in my dream...

412
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Good one.

413
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's not a joke, Waqar.

414
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Although it is like one.

415
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We don't need to meet those we want to meet.

416
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We meet those we think of.

417
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Now, I've got to meet Nano,

418
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But I can't meet her in my dreams.

419
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why?

420
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'd have to ask for her permission

421
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Even to meet her in my dreams.

422
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Go.

423
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She's in her room.

424
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who is it?

425
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's me, Nano.

426
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Gulrez.

427
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Come in, my dear.

428
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Here to meet me?

429
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yes, Nano.

430
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Skiving off work, eh?

431
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I just did...

432
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
When did that happen?

433
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've never seen you

434
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Skive off work.

435
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Something's changed, Nano...

436
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
They say great men aren't bound by habits and rules.

437
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Their habits keep changing,

438
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
As do their rules.

439
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've heard the same, too.

440
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But...

441
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who told you

442
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That you'd become a great man

443
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
By skiving off work?

444
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I thought

445
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I should do something

446
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That shows everyone

447
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That Gulrez means business.

448
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What are you up to?

449
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I had a dream...

450
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
A bolt from the blue...

451
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Bolt, eh, dear?

452
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm already in the middle of a thunderstorm.

453
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You'd better do something

454
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That gets me out of it.

455
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And that

456
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Is just what I'm here for.

457
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The dream was a sign...

458
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What are you saying?

459
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm honest, Nano.

460
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I saw an old man with a long white beard.

461
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He said,

462
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'There's two kinds of lovers'.

463
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'One, le peintre, working on his masterpiece of love'...

464
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Painter'!

465
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ah, yes...

466
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Painter'...

467
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And the other?

468
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'And two, the kind who buy masterpieces to adorn their walls with'.

469
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So, which one

470
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Would you be?

471
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Certes, not the one

472
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who'd buy a painting to adorn my wall with...

473
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So...

474
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What'd you do?

475
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I...

476
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'd just paint my masterpiece.

477
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm done with it now.

478
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
My story ends there.

479
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And...

480
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who'd adorn his wall with your painting?

481
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Waqar.

482
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Waqar Ahmed.

